      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": null,
      "message": "Arrays can be a good reason to use bash or korn shell but there is often another better solution.\nFor small usages, there is often a custom solution  more efficient than arrays.\nGeneric patterns given as examples of drop-in replacement are usually less efficient than using bash arrays and must be avoided when possible.\n\n\nHere are some pointers\nhttps://mywiki.wooledge.org/Bashism#arrays\nhttp://www.etalabs.net/sh_tricks.html => working_with_arrays",
